<item>
            <title>[FLINK-10772] create_binary_release.sh is broken</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-10772</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;create_binary_release.sh&lt;/tt&gt; is broken because it calls a script which does not exist. In fact, this script no longer needs to be called. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Moreover, the build fails because we skip the compilation and packaging of test dependencies via &lt;tt&gt;-Dmaven.test.skip=true&lt;/tt&gt;. The problem is that test dependencies are still being resolved if this property is specified. See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAR-138&quot; title=&quot;jar:test-jar is skipped when maven.test.skip=true&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MJAR-138&quot;&gt;MJAR-138&lt;/a&gt; for more information.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13196121">FLINK-10772</key>
